author: @star_tree304
text:
사람들의 편견 속에서 저 자리까지 올라가기란 쉽지 않을텐데... 
'쟤네는 방탄소년단 직속 후배 그룹이니까, 잘 하는 게 당연하지.'
'아이돌이면 원래 다 잘 해야지.'
유독 아이돌에게만 냉정한 사람들의 기준이기에 그 속에서 얼마나 마음이 미어지고 아팠을까... 하는 생각이 듭니다. 
아이돌도 데뷔하기 전에는 하나의 사람이에요. 결국 본질은 우리와 다르지 않다는 거죠. 
다만 굳이 차이점이라고 하자면 좀 더 전문적인 교육을 받았다는 것 뿐이죠. 생각을 해보세요. 어떤 한 학생이 서울대에 다니는 형에게 교육을 받았어요. 그런다고 그 아이의 성적이 형처럼 금방 좋아지고, 그만큼 될 수 있을까요? 그럴 수도, 그러지 않을 수도 있겠죠.
제가 하고 싶은 말은, 사람에 따라 다르다는 거예요. 성공한 사람은, 연예인들은 공통적으로 한 가지가 있죠, 최소한. 바로 '노력'. 남들보다 죽을만큼 노력해서 이 자리까지 올라온 사람들이에요. 그런 노력을, 우리가 그들의 음악을 듣고, 그들의 작품을 감상한다고 가볍게 말해서는 안 된다고 생각합니다. 
그게 진정으로 그들을 위하는 일일테니까요.

text: First of all, what a cute drunk moment we had here, I loved this interview, they seem like genuine and down-to-earth guys. There's something I'd like to highlight and it's been bothering me for a while. As an only army, things like this are none of my business, however, I'm glad yoongi talked about this, about how people compare txt with BTS. I saw a nasty article a while ago and I saw moas speaking up about it on Twitter, it's infuriating when the media and ignorant fans just dismiss all the hard work and the passion txt puts into their music, just because they're under the same company as bangtan, it's annoying af to think they don't deserve what they have, they do, they very much do! . I'm not part of their fandom, but I'm an outsider who has been watching them work since day 1. I want to congratulate moas and txt for the things you're achieving with the last album and I wish from the bottom of my heart only success for them, hard work is not always enough, but teamwork always makes the dream work, never forget that. I'm quietly rooting for you, sending lots of love 👏✨

author: @chocopop01
text: It's true, there is no other group out there like BTS.  A lot of artists have a hard time giving generously to up and coming artists because they're worried about being replaced and they want to stay relevant so they withhold information they've acquired in order to maintain their own status.  But BTS is so genuinely kind and thoughtful that they go out of their way to mentor other artists and look for ways to take care of the next generation.  It's really quite remarkable the scope of their generosity in caring for others. 💜💜💜 We see how well they've cared for one another since they became a group.  All from different backgrounds and they gave of themselves to each other. 💜💜💜 Every time I think of Jin being the maknae of his family and being treated as such to suddenly being the eldest of the group and the way he took care of Jungkookie from the very beginning and gave him the love and nurturing as the maknae that he was accustomed to receiving always makes my heart swell.  Jin was so selfless on behalf of the group and it wasn't just JK that he took care of and nurtured, it was the whole maknae line that he did that for.  He put himself in harms way to take care of Jimin when Jimin was being threatened....😢😭💜 And it's clear that they all put the group ahead of themselves to do what is in the best interest of the group as a whole and no one member tries to outshine the others.  They all shine and have so much talent to offer and they all support and lift up one another.  They really are great examples of how to balance pride with humility and how to be of service to others. 💜💜💜 It's no wonder that Army feels so much love for them because even though most of us will never meet them personally and so many have never had the opportunity yet to see them perform live, we still feel that same sort of nurturing from BTS that they give to those they meet personally.  They still very much concern themselves with taking care of Army that they feel about taking care of anyone else in their orbit.  It's really special and I just love these guys so much.

author: @parkgimmy4225
text:
Its the fact that people forget that TXT became trainees even before BTS got so big.

And tbh, at first, TXT were just the "brother group of BTS" for me too. I supported them but i didn't pay much attention to them. I would try to find some similarities between the two groups as well.
But last year, i finally gave TXT a chance and soon i stopped seeing them as just "the brother group of BTS". They now have their own identity in my mind. And although I'm not a Moa, i can still appreciate the amazing discography that they have. 
Comparison with BTS is something that couldn't have been avoided but it's because TXT were so capable themselves that they were able to make a name of their own.

"Farewell Neverland" by txt. It's about letting go of staying in neverland (hiding from your problems) It's the last song of their album Name Chapter Temptation,  it's also the last song in the album and the resolution. 
Just like their last album where thursday's child was about stages of grief this Temptation album is the stages of falling into then leaving neverland ( stopping your oblivion to the real world and facing reality ) or growing up and stop flying in oblivion and starting to come down to earth and touch grass but some say that it can be stagss of falling into then leaving addiction.


I know this was long but I just wanted to help ❤😅

author: @afnanel5485
text:
I'm re-watching this episode. The first time I watched it, I was thrown away by TXT cuteness. But now, I'm more analyzing and processing Suga's words. His words are so wise and eloquent, and his mindset is so enlightening. "You can’t not change. Change is inevitable, what matters is how you change." Those are words of wisdom. He's so true to himself. I aspire to be like that when I reach 30. I'm at that age when he was full of anger and just lost. On IU Palette, he said that he's not like that anymore and that he's calmer these days, and we can clearly see it. He's lighter and balanced, and more talkative.
 If you listen to his songs clearly, you'll see how he's always been criticizing and analyzing the world and how that has paid off eventually, personally, and professionally.

text:
何度も見ています。最初は3人がただただ可愛くて楽しくて見ていたけど、MOAとして、TXTが「頂点を目指して行くぞ」と5人で決心したと言ってくれたのが本当に嬉しかったです。
そう思っているのを感じてはいたけど、それを叶えるのはどれだけ大変なことか…HYBE所属だからこそ口にすることさえ易しいことではないのも分かっていました。
でも、5人が決心して船に乗ってくれたなら、MOAはエンジンでもスクリューでも、TXTが望む全ての物になります！

コンサート会場も、1位も初動も、もっと早く夢を叶えてあげられなくてごめんなさい。
でも、明日もその先もずっとMOAでいるし、夢が目標になり、目標が現実になるその日まで、ずっと一緒にいると約束します。

絶対に頂点に立とう、TXT&MOA！

author: @markys99
text: Esse vídeo me deixou feliz de um jeito INEXPLICÁVEL. Primeiro, eu queria agradecer ao Yoongi, por sempre ser alguém tão bom com os meninos do TXT. Ele parece realmente cuidar e se importar com eles, e eu me sinto tão grata:(( A minha história com o BTS é muito curta, mas eu fui uma grande fã. Eu fui uma Army, apesar de que muitos armys não vão aceitar que eu use esse termo já que eu não sou mais do fandom.. Bem, enfim. Eu fui Army por 2 anos, e foi realmente incrível. Eu conheci o BTS como nunca. Hoje em dia, eu conheço todas as histórias do grupo, os momentos tristes e felizes, e principalmente, as músicas. (Eu amo a discografia do BTS, é magnífica). Sinto saudade deles. Em 2020, eu senti um sentimento muito forte quando ouvi Life goes on. Foi muito bom. Meu tempo como army foi muito bom, mas mesmo assim, de de uma forma ou de outra, eu tenho uma história com eles, (mesmo que pequena). E pra sempre vou ter um carinho por eles. Já o TXT, bem, acho que em meados de 2019 eu estava destinada a me tornar um Moa. Dito e feito. Amo tanto os meninos. É tão gratificante pra mim ter acompanhado de comeback a comeback, e foi ainda mais gratificante quando eu vi todo o esforço e trabalho duro deles serem reconhecidos nesse Cb. Eu já sinto saudades:( Arrisco dizer que foi o melhor Cb da carreira do TXT até agora, e eu não poderia estar mais feliz. Lá em junho do ano passado, eu chorei como louca nos primeiros dias de tour. Foi uma mistura de sentimentos. Amo a amizade e o respeito que o TXT e o BTS tem uns pelos outros, isso me faz muito feliz. É engraçado como no comecinho de tudo, lá quando eu era Army, eu vivia falando que o Yeonjun era meio que o "filho" do Taehyung/Yoongi, e o Taehyun do Taehyung/Jungkook. Aiai, mal sabia eu KSKSKSKS! De todavia, obrigado Yoongi por esse vídeo incrível, onde nós, Moas, (e até Armys♡) pudemos ouvir conversas muito profundas de ambos os lados, mil e um elogios direcionados tanto ao TXT quanto ao BTS, grandes explosões de admiração, e, é claro, o Yeonjun bêbado. KSKSKSKKS! Eu amo vocês!💙💜

text: Buenos días, wow me ha impresionado ver este programa, me encanta escuchar todas sus luchas, experiencias como grupo, buenas y malas que los han ayudado a crecer, he llegado a la conclusión que ustedes son seres humanos que no le hacen daño a nadie, no envidian el éxito de nada y nadie, siempre están allí para todo aquel que necesiten de ustedes, no sé porque en otros país se ven la cultura interesante y respetuosa que ustedes tienen, es de gran ejemplo para nosotros los que vivimos en América hablamos uno de los idiomas más importantes y no tenemos ese respeto por nosotros mismos y por el prójimo, no queremos que otros triunfen, que se superen no debemos ser egoístas.  Gracias por tu programa Suga eres un gran ser humano, me encanta que seas muy abierto con todos los jóvenes para que sean ejemplo de cosas positivas para todo el mundo, para sea vencidas las guerras, la violencia, la delincuencia, y sobre todo venir de hogares desintegrados, esto provoca grandes odios, resentimientos en el ser humano, el cual no deja que se supere y luche por lo que le apasiona, los talentos que Dios nos ha regalado, debemos explotarlos sé que nada es fácil, como dijo Suga se sufre mucho pero se llega a conquistar países y culturas diferentes. Those boys who were also there at those times and saw bts and their company growing to become an empire today. Those boys who is vividly loved and adored by bts. Those boys who also had the same dream and drive for their company to prosper as what it is today, just almost same as everything bts had been through.
That's why for me if you are a fan who saw bts from their nugudom, you may not stan txt but there is no way you will dislike them, if you are then you haven't totally appreciated bts' struggles and how they are appalled to txt who also had the same struggles with them.

It was so hard on them, Maze in the Mirror (album Eternity) came from their hurt of that moment. It annoys me that a lot of people online will make up things about them when we know the real story. I'm just glad TXT debuted. Even though life is always hard on them, and people's expectations are crushing, I'm glad we have TXT.

author: @chatrandibujosfelices
text: Los primeros quince minutos quería llorar y los últimos minutos no podía dejar de reírme. Este episodio fue muy bonito para mi corazón de ARMOA, aunque todavía soy bebé Moa. Me sentí muy feliz de ver lo bueno que es Suga con sus compañeros más jóvenes y triste de saber que TXT también sufrieron como aprendices. Tanto BTS como TXT han tenido momentos difíciles, se han esforzado y han crecido mucho y eso se nota en la calidad de sus presentaciones y de su música. Por eso me entristece que haya algunas only Armys que ataquen a TXT o que nos odien a  las que no somos only Armys por apoyar a TXT, cuando la realidad es que ellos y BTS son como hermanos y lo único que quieren es que a todos les vaya bien y que todos tengan un buen futuro. Lo que hemos visto en este video, y lo agradecidos que son los más jóvenes con los mayores, es la razón por la que nosotras como fans tenemos que respetar a todas las bandas.

author: @mikellyartisan1384
text: I know that they want to perform at bigger stages for MOA, but I went to their concert last year in Sugarland, Texas, and it was sooooo nice being able to see them in a smaller venue (about 6k capacity). I'm actually glad I got to see them before they do big stadium concerts because the whole thing just felt more personal to me and I could see them a lot better. They were also able to actually run around the venue and interact with MOA and it was such a great experience. I know they'll be selling out stadiums in their future tours, but I did adore being able to attend their concerts while the venue was still small.

author: @meomeozzi5817
text:
Мне очень нравится то, как контактируют Юнги и Тэхен. Они оба говорят очень важные вещи как и для себя, так и для нас - людей, которые стремятся к своей мечте тяжелыми усилиями. И даже если у вас нет мечты - глядя на то, как усердно работают парни, вы набираетесь силы идти дальше. Даже когда тяжело. И я думаю, это так же помогает трейни (или айдолам, которые уже дебютировали) набраться сил и сказать себе "- Все, что я делаю - это не напрасно!"
То, как Ёнджун говорит о ценности мемберов, о каких-то рабочих моментах, в которых он сомневается и Юнги направляет его, словно светлячок в гуще леса действительно мило. Он такой застенчивый, но правда работает очень усердно (Даже если он так и не считает. Все участники ТХТ работаю не покладая рук, я правда горжусь ими)  
Приятно видеть, как они обсуждают какие-то переживания и моменты, которые оказали на них большие впечатления. 
Со временем забываешь, что это интервью и кажется, что сидишь с ними за общим столом, слушая приятельские истории и их переживания/откровения.  
Мне так же приятно видеть, какой у них спокойно и расслабленно проходит диалог.  Очень понравилось интервью и надеюсь увидеть позже и других участников группы. Спасибо Шуге за такую возможность!

author: @LotusFrog_n_Sun
text: It's mind blowing that YEONJUN & TAEHYUN would not know how hard Suga (& other BTS members) struggled to get to the point where TXT is now (so early on in TXT's career ! ) It made me cringe when they expressed thier disappointment about having had small venues & stages. I am NOT throwing shade at  them  because no doubt they have talent & work hard, Yet when TXT debuted, they came out like a cannonball because of all the resources available to them. (The "house" that BTS built 😜) BTS and ARMY's support has had a part of thier success, especially initially.  The struggles that BTS went through , they used as a catapult to get where they are now. "Entitled" is a bit strong & negative a term to use but I hope TXT are able to avoid that mindset & embrace the "process" of growth through adversity, letting the hard & disappointing things fuel them to more success that will be more precious because of how it was earned.

author: @Madam_De_Pompadour
text:
Это официально самый милый и трогательный выпуск! И то как Шуга заботлив к младшим, и то как они искренне этому благодарны...
И темы, которые они обсуждали были такими серьёзными и глубокими... То через что проходят совсем ещё юные трейни ради своей мечты... Как Ёнджун рассказывал что они разбавляли бесплатную газировку водой чтобы хватило на всех, про эти старые тренировочные залы в подвалах... просто сердце кровью обливается...
Конечно пройдя через всё это - все айдолы заслуживают ту безмерную любовь уважение и благодарность, которую им дарят их фанаты.
И Шуга прекрасен, действительно прекрасный человек и хён для младших, который не стал слишком гордым и высокомерным от своей славы, а всегда помнит как ему эта слава досталась, сколько он ради этого работал... и так же искренне теперь поддерживает молодое поколение, которое проходит тот же путь!
Искренне восхищаюсь им как человеком❤

Seeing this made me teary...TXT was there like at the exact moment when I started to feel my life was meaningless and to see them here talking about their story was just a special moment for me. Suga's words and the fact that TXT's hyungs are there to tell them the words which we as fans cannot convey in person is just so comforting to know.  
As a MOA I would like to reiterate the fact that YES TXT came from a privileged point of view with BTS's major support and they will always acknowledge it and live up to people's expectation with double the hard work, especially the expectations of their BTS hyungs who were there to give a push to them towards a brighter future.

author: @milee1780
text:
Tengo que decir que cuando me entere del debut de TXT estaba muy feliz
Mis chicos tenían tanto tiempo siendo el único grupo de su empresa y de seguro debió ser solitario, aunque ahora siempre reciben cumplidos por donde vayan no siempre fue así y no tener en quien apoyarse tuvo que ser difícil, claro estamos los fans pero hay un tipo de relación que solo pueden tener los artistas. Cuando esos 5 niños llegaron estaba tan preocupada porque sabía el tipo de comentarios que iban a recibir, pero aunque se notaba que les afectaba siempre les oía responder con seguridad que se esforzarían para demostrar su propio valor y hacer a BTS orgulloso. Me sentí aliviada porque supe que ahora nuestros Tannies tendría a unos chicos tan humildes y trabajadores como hoobaes, les agradezco por expresarse como lo hacen de BTS y  estoy segura que ellos son un gran apoyo para el uno para el otro. Han crecido bien niños, lo están haciendo bien, tienen muchas canciones increíbles y sé que llegaran aún más lejos, TXT fifhting!!!

author: @xionnyx3337
text:
😂😂😂
Son demasiado adorables los tres juntos. Ya de por sí era adorable escuchar a Jimin diciendo que son sus bebés y ahora verlos con Yoongi, realmente son re lindos. Está es una de las cosas que más me gusta de SUGA, puede parecerte alguien serio o alguien que puede molestarse fácilmente, pero la realidad es que es un lindo gatito. Siempre estoy agradecida con Yoongi por hablar de las cosas que le han preocupado, molestado, de lo que ha dudo u experimentado y ver cómo eso lo ha ido compartido con sus juniors es de lo más lindo. No todos son capaces de ayudar a otros con sinceridad y siempre habrá dudas acerca de como seguir adelante, no es fácil ir con consejos y estoy segura que sin ellos es aún más difícil. 
Recuerdo cuando debutaron estos chicos (TXT) todo mundo hablaba de sus expectativas al venir de la misma empresa que BTS, que presión debieron recibir en ese entonces. Me gustan sus canciones, son muy de mi estilo musical. También, me alegro que se lleven bien con Hobi, Jiminie y Yoongie, ellos son de las personas más cálidas, estoy segura que estarán apoyando a estos chicos de la forma que puedan.
Espero que les siga yendo bien en su carrera.

아니 나 왜 눈물나냐 …

사실 이런 얘기들을 진짜 사적으로 따로 만나서 얘기하는게 아닌 카메라 앞에서 하는건 팬들도 이 마음들 이 진심을 알아줬으면 좋겠고 그들이 이뤄나가는 것들이 아티스트와 팬이 함께 의지하며 걸어가는 길이기 때문이겠죠
연준이만큼의 그릇을 가지고 연준만큼의 노력을 하고 연준만큼의 의지와 열정을 가진 사람이 없다는것도 무슨말인지 너무나 이해되고
연준태현은 성공에 대한 야망과 독기를 가졌지만 5명의 목표가 같지 않았어도 무대 완성도, 음원, 라이브 퀄리티, 퍼포먼스, 비주얼, 컨셉, 프로듀싱, 팬들과의 소통, 팬들의 행복 등 각자가 원하는 모든 것들이 다른 방향이라고 생각하지 않아요 각자 생각하는 방향이 달라도 같은 길로 이끌어줄 거라고 생각하고 그게 투바투의 정체성이고 모아가 사랑하는 모든 것들이고요
열정과 의지를 가지고 더욱더 전진하려고 하는 모든 노력이 너희를 앞으로 나아가게 하는것같아
너희는 편견을 넘어서고 기대를 채운 그룹이야

I remember when I only keep BTS and OOR songs on my phone, and my friend ask “is this all?” I said, yeah, and she asked again “why?”

“Because I like them, duh.”

“I mean, you don’t like idol from another company? Like JYP or YG?”

“No? I don’t like them. I only like BTS, and, maybe one day, when bighit had another idol group.”

I remember saying it with full confidence. And 3 years later, I finally experiencing the thrills when you wait a group to debut. The second “CROWN” released, I fell in love. Not just crown, the whole album! 

So yeah, HYBE’s artists built different, indeed.

author: @lillianelightwood6464
text:
@@BvstJungkookist ella está hablando precisamente que los fans hacen comparaciones pelotudas. Acaso alguien negó que la vida de los tannies era complicada? No, TODOS SABEMOS SUS COMIENZOS., el comentario NUNCA minimizó su experiencia. Cuál es el gusto de estar a la defensiva che? 
El comentario se refiere a que así como BTS tuvo sus PROPIOS problemas TXT tenía otro, eran el único grupo después de ellos así que la expectativa estaba ahí, tenían que ser iguales o mejores, ellos tampoco la tuvieron fácil,  por el hecho de que tenían que salir debajo del nombre de BTS, no eran tan conocidos al principio y un montón de “fans” los lleno de hate llamándolos bts wannabes o copias baratas, CUANDO ELLOS JAMÁS BUSCARON COPIAR A SUS SUNBAENIMS. Los llenaron de odio siendo adolescents (si si igual que todos los idols, eso no quiere decir que esta bien) los llamaban flojos, nepobabys y demás, cuando ellos también tienen su esfuerzo que merecen reconocer. No todos los obstáculos constan de morirse de hambre y sufrir cortes económicos, y eso no los hace menos merecedores de aplausos. LOS PROBLEMAS NO SON COMPETENCIAS.

text:
슈가님이 하고 싶었던 말을 다 해주시는 것 같으셔서 마음이 편하다.
데뷔를 하고 기사 하나가 날 때 '방탄 후배그룹' 이라는 타이틀이 생기고 첫 문장이  '신인 그룹 투모로우바이투게더' 가 아닌 '방탄소년단의 후배 그룹 투모로우바이투게더' 라고 적혀있어서 조금 안타까웠던것 같다... 
물론 아미분들과 방탄분들이 주신 응원과 사랑이 너무 감사하고 넘쳐났지만 언제까지 방탄의 후배라는 타이틀을 가지고 활동할까, 라는 사실에 나도 확신이 서지 않았던 것 같은데 이렇게 멋진 그룹으로 성장해줘서 너무 고맙다....
이제는 '4세대의 대표 주자 그룹 투모로우바이투게더' 라는 타이틀을 가지고 계속 케이팝을 이끌어 나가주는 그룹이 되어줘서 너무 고맙고 사랑해.
슈가님도, 방탄도, 아미분들도 우리 투바투 그리고 모아까지도 항상 행복하길......

author: @n_equam
text:
This episode was honestly everything to me. I love both groups so much, each in their own way and I have my own story with each one, so the fact that they are actually this close made me feel very warm. I’m so glad TXT has such seniors, which obviously adds pressure and made it especially hard for them in the beginning, but there’s objectively no one else with as much experience as BTS. They’ve really seen it all, endured and are still going strong in their 10th year, absolutely determined to keep going for many many years coming forward. You really couldn’t ask for a better mentor. And I’m glad TXT is there for BTS, too, to remind them of their legacy, shower them with praise and remind them how young and passionate BTS themselves always were. I’m so glad they have each other 

For some reason I’m also glad they never truly shared this closeness with us. They just didn’t feel the need to, and that’s why everything in this video feels so genuine. They’ve both suffered so much in their own ways - and oh, they’re definitely self-aware - but I feel like they really value the team over everything else and that’s what makes both TXT and BTS seem so stable and confident in their own future. I can’t wait to share my future with both of them, too 🤍

P. S. “You supported us from the top” and them sharing their struggles as the screen shows both lightsticks next to each other… oh, my poor heart can barely handle this

author: @soobinsgirl
text:
My key takeaways while I watched this screaming in my room:
♥ TXT are so freaking humble and thankful. I really love the hungry mindset of wanting to improve and chase their dreams, and I want to continue to be inspired by them.
♥ 29:21 The way the audio director lowered Yeonjun's volume but you can still hear him 웅냥웅냥ing beside Taehyun.
♥ 22:37 The way Yeonjun quietly spills half the drink out of his mouth sent me into outer space.
♥ 27:40 The way Yeonjun goes 왜 웃으세요?!?! made me kick my legs fr.
♥ 29:44 I love how Taehyun has his arm around his hyung. I'm so glad Taehyun was here because Yeonjun would not have made it through HAHAH
♥ 30:41 Yeonjun baby why are you still trying to sign the bottle, baby boy you signed on the glass already AND THAT ISN'T YOUR SIGNATURE HAHAHAH

♥ Overall, I'm so happy to stan TXT, from how concisely Taehyun talks about his life, his own experiences, and his love for MOA to me getting drunk on how INSANELY CUTE Yeonjun is, especially since even drunk you can see not just how much he loves MOA but also his members. I will never stop complimenting him until he sees how MOA sees him. 

But most of all I love how much TXT loves TXT. ♥

author: @shyramohsin
text:
i had to take so many breaks from watching because if i didn't, i would have ended up crying and i cannot afford another mental breakdown rn. finally finished watching this 30-minute video after almost 2 hours... ;; i'll have to watch this again some day without breaks to fully appreciate everything, but even as is rn, i feel so happy to have started stanning txt.

i'm j a baby moa who started stanning them when srr promotions were j beginning, so i still have a lot about all members to learn and a lot of txt's history to understand, but yeonjun and taehyun's love for moas, bts, and of course, txt, was so overwhelming. personally, i have, and still do, have a certain kind of boundary between idols and fans that i keep to - it's j a way to make sure there's no dependency and a constant reality check, of course, but the way yeonjun and taehyun were talking about moas made my heart so full. the pure sincerity and appreciation they have for all moas was just... wow.

as two of the members who have the most ambition for the team, it's so wonderful to see them appear together and talk about their hopes and dreams for the team. their dreams for the team will always be supported by the others too, but i genuinely do just hope they all take care of themselves. aiming for the top is natural in most humans, but i just hope they don't forget about their health. i'm sure moas would love to see them succeed without overbearing pain, first and foremost! i understand their passion, but i do hope that they can also constantly see their progress instead of seeing what they're currently lacking.

anyways, i'm really so glad i started stanning txt, and i can't wait for a day when i get to be a part of the sea of moas to see them perform live in front of me.

Este episodio me ha dejado maravillada. Me ha dejado ver una vez más la gran persona que es Suga, en definitiva, se esta volviendo una persona a la que admiro demasiado, más allá de su música.
Y de mis hermosos TXT, como MOA que también soy, ver esta cara de ellos, en donde se miran relajados y tan ellos, donde se ven libres de expresar lo que piensan y sienten sin temor a criticas, son momentos que me llenan al corazón.

Todos son, verdaderamente, increíbles. 
Amo mucho a Suga,  aTae y  a Yeyo <3
